        "comments": [
          {
            "text": "...And Polgar would have reached her wanted position but with White to move!\n\nThis is how triangulation is done. \n\nYou get the enemy king to its best defensive square, but with them to move. Therefore, they have to move the king away. ",
            "arrows": null,
            "highlights": {
