          "JJ"
        ],
        "comments": [
          {
            "text": "So how can Judit reach the position where the kings are on c3 and b5 but it's White to move?\n\nThis is where the concept called triangulation is used. \n\nBlack will make a triangle with her king and lose a tempo. That way, when the wanted position is reached, it will be White to play! \n\nThe first step is to move the king to c7 or b7, it's the same.",
            "arrows": {
              "threats": [],
              "opportunities": [
                "c7-b7",
                "b7-b6"
              ]
            },
            "highlights": null
          }
